<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Gradient Background Example</title>
  <link
    href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />
</head>
<body>

  <div class="container py-5">
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-center">Gradient Background with Dark Theme</h1>

    <div class="p-5 bg-dark bg-gradient text-white rounded">
      <h2>Welcome to the Community Portal</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        This section uses <code>bg-dark</code> combined with <code>bg-gradient</code> and white text.
      </p>
      <p>
        The gradient creates a subtle shading effect over the dark background, improving aesthetics while maintaining readability.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
  ></script>
</body>
</html>
